@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`. The fallback payload now keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and the router normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before calling the preview builder.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code path existed here; the reopened fallback regression was fixed once in the shared preview payload flow.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete. The suggestion targets an outdated diff hunk and would reintroduce a legacy branch that is not part of the current remediation. It was intentionally not applied.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression test covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` through `build_policy_preview(...)`, asserting the fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback example now shows `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`, matching the corrected payload.
